## Key implementation notes (from 2026-05-31 bug fix):
# BUG1 FIX: ALFWorldEnv.build_student_prompt / build_teacher_prompt added.
#   Root cause: train_cell called env.build_student_prompt() for ALL envs; ALFWorld didn't have it.
# BUG2 FIX (CUDA OOM): Reduced batch_size from 4→1 for search_qa (keeps G=8 rollouts).
#   Root cause: batch=4×G=8=32 seqs × 1024 tokens held 8 mini-batches of fp32 logprobs
#   ([4,1024,151K]×4bytes=2.47GB each = 19.7GB total) in computation graph simultaneously.
#   Fix: batch=1×G=8=8 seqs → 2 mini-batches → 2×1.85GB=3.7GB logprobs. Fits!
#   Also: max_new_tokens search_qa 512→256; grad_ckpt enabled for 1.7B too.
# BUG3 FIX: Added gc.collect() to OOM handler to force Python GC before empty_cache.
# BUG4 FIX: Free bf16 logits (del logits) before computing fp32 logprobs in _compute_logp_chunk.
# - gradient checkpointing now enabled for ALL models (was only 3B+7B)
# - BETA=10.0, LAMBDA=0.1, gate = sigmoid(BETA*delta).detach() [stop-gradient]
# - 7B model still expected to OOM (model+grads=28GB > 24GB A5000) — cells recorded as failed
